insta_description:
#Repost another pic for @locusgear
・・・
Djedi CTB Dome prototype, field test at Eastern Sierra, California. 
This is made by cutting-edge material which is combined with Non-woven Dyneema fabric and eVent membrane. And it has breathable and water proof capability along with very strong breaking strength. Of course, this structure is made by no-seam bonding method.

Photo by @pascalshirley 
ジェダイ CTB ドーム プロトタイプ、カリフォルニア州イースタン・シエラでのフィールドテスト。これはダイニーマ繊維の不織布とイーヴェントのメンブレンを組み合わせた最先端の素材で作られています。透湿性と防水性があり、超軽量ながら強い破断強度を備えています。もちろん、この構造はシームレスのボンディング・メソッドを用いて作られています。

insta_description:
Congrats to my buddy @chandlerleekane for launching his new venture www.stealthbackcountry.com  I look forward to many more years of riding together! ・・・Repost 
After 5 years of countless research, riding, and organizing trips to Hokkaido Japan, I'm launching @stealth_backcountry to bring like minded people together in search of the deepest, lightest snow of their lives. We will be based in Central Hokkaido as to avoid the crowds and with 5 different resorts to choose from, we are able to access the deepest snow Hokkaido has to offer. Our website is live and link is in bio. The outpouring support from friends and family has allowed me to have 3 of 6 weeks already booked out this year. Big thanks to @pascalshirley for the imagery over the years, to the @gentemstick family for your kind words and encouragement, to @namasuteyama @sharkboysharkboy @pepe_films_ for joining me in this adventure, to @chris_christenson73 who 5 years ago let me in on this secret, @ianvotteri for your social media expertise, along with all the friends who have believed in me and joined in previous trips. Arigato Gozaimasu #stealthbackcountry #hokkaido #japan #japow #japanuary #powderdojo #gentemstick #skiing #snowboarding

insta_description:
First food blog: 
So if any of you are familiar with the Chocolate Emporium, they’re very famous with their huge decorative milkshakes. Monday night, I went there with a couple of friends and it was worth it. The line was huge and people were tempted. I ordered the ‘Espresso Buzzz’ and yes you can guess right, it’s exactly very tempting and big and decorative. While the taste was exactly like coffee, the surrounding and the inside of it had a spread of hazelnut whipped cream topped with coffee beans, pieces of biscotti, and a classy cherry on top. All in all, I’d rate it a 5/5 for everything, but a suggestion for everyone: share the drink with someone, don’t have it to yourself because we all know we can’t finish a drink that consists of at least 100 grams of sugar! -

Probably the only place I’d go to get burgers that fit my preference. BurgerFI has all the type of burgers it has to offer, but since as a Muslim I can’t have any of their meats, they provide me meatless burgers. One in particular would be the VegeFi Burger which consists of quinoa patty. Also, I’d recommend to get their fries topped with garlic+parmesan. Everything was so delicious, and the staff were very friendly. 5/5 for everything. -

insta_description:
Food blog #3: Saigon Noodle and Grill
A lot can be said about this place. Food, hospitality, themes, and taste. Saigon Noodle and Grill, based in Downtown Orlando, has a variety of dishes for everyone. But for Halal eaters (like me), only depend on 2 dishes that do not contain pork, chicken, or beef. Although I ordered vegetable soup with rice noodles and vegetable spring rolls, it was worth it. Just remember to add a little bit of soy sauce and sriracha sauce to the bowl. And if you have trouble what you’re looking for, the servers are always there to help you out. Ask for a guy named Tony. He’s always there to help out. 
Rating 5/5 -

insta_description:
Ever since starting UCF, I’ve thought about earning an internship so I can finally put my feet out the door. That hasn’t happened yet, and most of the time whenever I felt like giving up, that wasn’t the best option for me. “Giving up leads to failure, and failure doesn’t fit me properly” is my motto in life. So to everyone who has givin’ up on accomplishing their goals, don’t quit yet. Surround yourself with positive people who actually care about you to accomplish those goals, instead of the ones who tell you straight up that “you’re sh*t”.
